content:
This file defines the Settings page for the DocMed application, allowing users to manage their profile and billing information.

## Purpose

The Settings page provides a centralized location for users to update their account details and manage their subscription. It utilizes a tabbed interface to separate profile management from billing information.

## Key Components and Functionality

-   **`SettingsPage` Component:** The main component for the settings page. It manages the active tab state using `useState` and renders different content based on the selected tab.
-   **Tabbed Interface:** Implemented using `TabButton` components. Users can switch between 'Profile' and 'Billing' tabs.
    -   **`TabButton` Component:** A reusable button component for the tab navigation. It highlights the active tab and displays an icon.
-   **Profile Tab:** Integrates with Clerk's `UserProfile` component for managing user account details. It includes extensive `appearance` props to customize the UI of the Clerk component, aligning it with the DocMed design system.
-   **Billing Tab:** Currently displays a `BillingPlaceholder` component, indicating that billing management features are under development.
    -   **`BillingPlaceholder` Component:** A UI element that informs the user that billing management is coming soon and what features will be available in the future.

## Usage Example

When a user navigates to the `/dashboard/settings` route, they will see the Settings page. Initially, the 'Profile' tab will be active, displaying the `UserProfile` component. Users can click the 'Billing' tab to view the placeholder message for payment management.

```tsx
// Example of how SettingsPage is rendered within the application
// This component would typically be placed within a layout that provides
// navigation and potentially other common dashboard elements.

import SettingsPage from './app/dashboard/settings/page';

function DashboardLayout() {
  return (
    <div className="flex">
      {/* Navigation Sidebar */}
      <nav>
        {/* ... */}
      </nav>
      <main className="flex-1">
        <SettingsPage />
      </main>
    </div>
  );
}

export default DashboardLayout;
```
